#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the LINSTOR Controller"
msgstr "複数のLINSTORコントローラー"

#. type: Table
msgid "  The LINSTOR Controller has a configuration file that is and has to be placed into the following path: `/etc/linstor/linstor.toml`.  A recent configuration example can be found here: https://github.com/LINBIT/linstor-server/blob/master/docs/linstor.toml-example[`linstor.toml-example`] [[s-linstor-rest-api]]"
msgstr "LINSTOR Controllerには、以下のパスに配置される必要がある設定ファイルがあります：`/etc/linstor/linstor.toml`。 最新の設定例はこちらで見つけることができます： https://github.com/LINBIT/linstor-server/blob/master/docs/linstor.toml-example[`linstor.toml-example`]。[[s-linstor-rest-api]]"

#. type: Title ====
#, no-wrap
msgid "LINSTOR REST API"
msgstr "LINSTOR REST API"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"To make LINSTOR's administrative tasks more accessible and also available for web-frontends a\n"
"REST API has been created. The REST API is embedded in the LINSTOR controller and since LINSTOR\n"
"0.9.13 configured through the `linstor.toml` configuration file.\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"LINSTORの管理タスクをよりアクセスしやすくし、Webフロントエンドでも利用可能にするために、REST APIが作成されました。このREST APIはLINSTORコントローラに組み込まれており、LINSTOR 0.9.13以降では`linstor.toml`設定ファイルで構成されています。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[http]\n"
"  enabled = true\n"
"  port = 3370\n"
"  listen_addr = \"127.0.0.1\"  # to disable remote access\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"[http]\n"
"  enabled = true\n"
"  port = 3370\n"
"  listen_addr = \"127.0.0.1\"  # to disable remote access\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
msgid "  If you want to use the REST API the current documentation can be found on the following link: https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis-docs/Linstor/Linstor/ [[s-linstor-rest-api-https]]"
msgstr "REST APIを使用したい場合は、現在のドキュメントは次のリンクで見つけることができます: https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis-docs/Linstor/Linstor/"

#. type: Title ====
#, no-wrap
msgid "LINSTOR REST API HTTPS"
msgstr "LINSTOR REST API HTTPS"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"The HTTP REST API can also run secured by HTTPS and is highly recommended if you use any\n"
"features that require authorization. To do so you have to create a Java keystore file with a\n"
"valid certificate that will be used to encrypt all HTTPS traffic.\n"
"\n"
"Here is a simple example on how you can create a self signed certificate with the `keytool` that\n"
"is included in the Java Runtime:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"HTTP REST APIはHTTPSでセキュリティを確保することも可能であり、認証が必要な機能を使用する場合は強くお勧めします。そのためには、すべてのHTTPSトラフィックを暗号化するために使用される有効な証明書を持つJavaのキーストアファイルを作成する必要があります。以下は、Javaランタイムに含まれる`keytool`を使用して自己署名証明書を作成する簡単な例です。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keytool -keyalg rsa -keysize 2048 -genkey -keystore ./keystore_linstor.jks\\\n"
" -alias linstor_controller\\\n"
" -dname \"CN=localhost, OU=SecureUnit, O=ExampleOrg, L=Vienna, ST=Austria, C=AT\"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"keytool -keyalg rsa -keysize 2048 -genkey -keystore ./keystore_linstor.jks\\\n"
" -alias linstor_controller\\\n"
" -dname \"CN=localhost, OU=SecureUnit, O=ExampleOrg, L=Vienna, ST=Austria, C=AT\"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"`keytool` will ask for a password to secure the generated keystore file and is needed for the\n"
"LINSTOR Controller configuration. In your `linstor.toml` file you have to add the following\n"
"section:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"`keytool`は、生成されたキーストアファイルを保護するためのパスワードを要求します。このパスワードはLINSTORコントローラーの構成に必要です。`linstor.toml`ファイルには、次のセクションを追加する必要があります: \n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[https]\n"
"  keystore = \"/path/to/keystore_linstor.jks\"\n"
"  keystore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"[https]\n"
"  keystore = \"/path/to/keystore_linstor.jks\"\n"
"  keystore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
msgid ""
"  Now (re)start the `linstor-controller` and the HTTPS REST API should be available on port 3371.  More information about how to import other certificates can be found here: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/tools/unix/keytool.html IMPORTANT: After enabling HTTPS access, all requests to the HTTP v1 REST API will be redirected to the HTTPS redirect. If your have not <<s-linstor-configuration-file-"
"specifying-controllers,specified a LINSTOR controller in the LINSTOR configuration TOML file>> (`/etc/linstor/linstor.toml`), then you will need to use a different syntax when using the LINSTOR client (`linstor`) as described in <<s-using_the_linstor_client>>.  [[s-rest-api-https-restricted-client]]"
msgstr ""
"今、`linstor-controller`を(再)起動させると、HTTPS REST APIがポート3371で利用可能になります。その他の証明書のインポート方法についてはこちらをご覧ください：https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/tools/unix/keytool.html　**重要**: HTTPSアクセスを有効にした後、HTTP v1 REST APIへのすべてのリクエストはHTTPSリダイレクトされます。もしLINSTORのコントローラを <<s-linstor-configuration-file-specifying-controllers,"
"LINSTOR設定TOMLファイル>> (`/etc/linstor/linstor.toml`)に指定していない場合、LINSTORクライアント(`linstor`)を使用する際に異なる構文を使用する必要があります。詳細は<<s-using_the_linstor_client, LINSTORクライアントの使用方法>>で説明されています。"

#. type: Title =====
#, no-wrap
msgid "LINSTOR REST API HTTPS Restricted Client Access"
msgstr "LINSTOR REST-API HTTPS 制限付きクライアントアクセス"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"Client access can be restricted by using a SSL/TLS truststore on the Controller. Basically you\n"
"create a certificate for your client and add it to your truststore and the client then uses this\n"
"certificate for authentication.\n"
"\n"
"First create a client certificate:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"コントローラー上でのクライアントアクセスは、SSL/TLS信頼ストアを使用して制限することができます。基本的には、クライアント用の証明書を作成し、それを信頼ストアに追加し、クライアントはこの証明書を認証に使用します。まず、クライアント証明書を作成します: \n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keytool -keyalg rsa -keysize 2048 -genkey -keystore client.jks\\\n"
" -storepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -alias client1\\\n"
" -dname \"CN=Client Cert, OU=client, O=Example, L=Vienna, ST=Austria, C=AT\"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"keytool -keyalg rsa -keysize 2048 -genkey -keystore client.jks\\\n"
" -storepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -alias client1\\\n"
" -dname \"CN=Client Cert, OU=client, O=Example, L=Vienna, ST=Austria, C=AT\"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"Next, import this certificate to your controller truststore:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"次に、この証明書をコントローラのトラストストアにインポートします。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keytool -importkeystore\\\n"
" -srcstorepass linstor -deststorepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -srckeystore client.jks -destkeystore trustore_client.jks\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"keytool -importkeystore\\\n"
" -srcstorepass linstor -deststorepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -srckeystore client.jks -destkeystore trustore_client.jks\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"And enable the truststore in the `linstor.toml` configuration file:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"そして `linstor.toml` 設定ファイルのトラストストアを有効にします。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[https]\n"
"  keystore = \"/path/to/keystore_linstor.jks\"\n"
"  keystore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"  truststore = \"/path/to/trustore_client.jks\"\n"
"  truststore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"[https]\n"
"  keystore = \"/path/to/keystore_linstor.jks\"\n"
"  keystore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"  truststore = \"/path/to/trustore_client.jks\"\n"
"  truststore_password = \"linstor\"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"Now restart the Controller and it will no longer be possible to access the controller API\n"
"without a correct certificate.\n"
"\n"
"The LINSTOR client needs the certificate in PEM format, so before you can use it, you have to\n"
"convert the java keystore certificate to the PEM format.\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"今、Controllerを再起動して、正しい証明書なしにController APIにアクセスすることはできなくなります。LINSTORクライアントはPEM形式の証明書が必要なので、それを使う前にjava keystore証明書をPEM形式に変換する必要があります。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Convert to pkcs12\n"
"keytool -importkeystore -srckeystore client.jks -destkeystore client.p12\\\n"
" -storepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -srcalias client1 -srcstoretype jks -deststoretype pkcs12\n"
"\n"
"# use openssl to convert to PEM\n"
"openssl pkcs12 -in client.p12 -out client_with_pass.pem\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"# Convert to pkcs12\n"
"keytool -importkeystore -srckeystore client.jks -destkeystore client.p12\\\n"
" -storepass linstor -keypass linstor\\\n"
" -srcalias client1 -srcstoretype jks -deststoretype pkcs12\n"
"\n"
"# use openssl to convert to PEM\n"
"openssl pkcs12 -in client.p12 -out client_with_pass.pem\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"To avoid entering the PEM file password all the time it might be convenient to remove the\n"
"password.\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"PEM ファイルのパスワードを常に入力しないようにするには、以下のようにします。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"openssl rsa -in client_with_pass.pem -out client1.pem\n"
"openssl x509 -in client_with_pass.pem >> client1.pem\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"openssl rsa -in client_with_pass.pem -out client1.pem\n"
"openssl x509 -in client_with_pass.pem >> client1.pem\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"Now this PEM file can easily be used in the client:\n"
"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"これでこの PEMファイルをクライアントで使用できるようになります。\n"
"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"linstor --certfile client1.pem node list\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"linstor --certfile client1.pem node list\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
msgid "  The `--certfile` parameter can also added to the client configuration file, see <<s-using_the_linstor_client>> for more details.  [[s-linstor-satellite-config]]"
msgstr "`--certfile`パラメーターは、クライアント構成ファイルにも追加できます。詳細については、<<s-using_the_linstor_client,リンストアクライアントの使用方法>>を参照してください。[[s-linstor-satellite-config]]"

#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring LINSTOR Satellite"
msgstr "LINSTOR Satellite の設定"

#. type: Table
msgid "  The LINSTOR Satellite software has an optional configuration file that uses the TOML file syntax and has to be put into the following path `/etc/linstor/linstor_satellite.toml`.  A recent configuration example can be found here: https://github.com/LINBIT/linstor-server/blob/master/docs/linstor_satellite.toml-example[linstor_satellite.toml-example] [[s-linstor-logging]]"
msgstr "LINSTOR Satelliteソフトウェアには、TOMLファイル構文を使用したオプションの設定ファイルがあり、次のパス`/etc/linstor/linstor_satellite.toml`に配置する必要があります。最新の設定例はこちらで確認できます: [linstor_satellite.toml-example](https://github.com/LINBIT/linstor-server/blob/master/docs/linstor_satellite.toml-example)。[[s-linstor-logging]]"

#. type: Title ===
#, no-wrap
msgid "Logging"
msgstr "ロギング"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"LINSTOR uses https://www.slf4j.org/[SLF4J] with https://logback.qos.ch/[logback] as binding.\n"
"This gives LINSTOR the possibility to distinguish between the log levels `ERROR`, `WARN`,\n"
"`INFO`, `DEBUG` and `TRACE` (in order of increasing verbosity). The following are\n"
"the different ways that you can set the logging level, ordered by priority (first has highest\n"
"priority):\n"
"\n"
". Since LINSTOR *client* version 1.20.1, you can use the command `controller set-log-level` to\n"
"  change the log level used by LINSTOR's running configuration. Various arguments can be used\n"
"  with this command. Refer to the command's `--help` text for details. For example, to set the\n"
"  log level to `TRACE` on the LINSTOR controller and all satellites, enter the following\n"
"  command:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"LINSTORは、https://www.slf4j.org/[SLF4J]を使用し、バインディングとしてhttps://logback.qos.ch/[logback]を使用しています。これにより、LINSTORは`ERROR`、`WARN`、 `INFO`、`DEBUG`、および`TRACE`（冗長性の増加順に並んだ）のログレベルを区別することが可能となります。以下に、優先順位で並べ替えられたログレベルを設定する方法がいくつか示されています:\n"
"LINSTORの*client*バージョン1.20.1以降、`controller set-log-level`コマンドを使用して、LINSTORの実行構成で使用されるログレベルを変更できます。このコマンドにはさまざまな引数が使用できます。詳細については、コマンドの`--help`テキストを参照してください。例えば、LINSTORコントローラーと全サテライトでログレベルを`TRACE`に設定する場合、次のコマンドを入力します:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ linstor controller set-log-level --global TRACE\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"$ linstor controller set-log-level --global TRACE\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+\n"
"To change the LINSTOR log level on a particular node, you can use the LINSTOR client (since\n"
"version 1.20.1) command `node set-log-level`.\n"
"+\n"
"NOTE: Changes that you make to the log level by using the LINSTOR client will not persist\n"
"LINSTOR service restarts, for example, if a node reboots.\n"
"\n"
". `TRACE` mode can be `enabled` or `disabled` using the debug console:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"+\n"
"バージョン1.20.1では、コマンド`node set-log-level`が追加されました。特定のノードでLINSTORのログレベルを変更するには、LINSTORクライアント（バージョン1.20.1以降）のコマンド`node set-log-level`を使用できます。\n"
"+\n"
"注意: LINSTORクライアントを使用して行ったログレベルの変更は、ノードが再起動する場合など、LINSTORのサービス再開時には継続しません。\n"
"\n"
". `TRACEモードは、デバッグコンソールを使用して`enabled（有効）`または`disabled（無効）`にできます:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Command ==> SetTrcMode MODE(enabled)\n"
"SetTrcMode           Set TRACE level logging mode\n"
"New TRACE level logging mode: ENABLED\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"Command ==> SetTrcMode MODE(enabled)\n"
"SetTrcMode           Set TRACE level logging mode\n"
"New TRACE level logging mode: ENABLED\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
". When starting the controller or satellite a command line argument can be passed:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"コントローラまたはサテライトを起動するときに、コマンドライン引数を渡すことができます。\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"java ... com.linbit.linstor.core.Controller ... --log-level TRACE\n"
"java ... com.linbit.linstor.core.Satellite  ... --log-level TRACE\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"java ... com.linbit.linstor.core.Controller ... --log-level TRACE\n"
"java ... com.linbit.linstor.core.Satellite  ... --log-level TRACE\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
". The recommended place is the `logging` section in the configuration file.  The default\n"
"  configuration file location is `/etc/linstor/linstor.toml` for the controller and\n"
"  `/etc/linstor/linstor_satellite.toml` for the satellite.  Configure the logging level as\n"
"  follows:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
". 推奨される場所は、設定ファイルの `logging` セクションです。コントローラのデフォルト設定ファイルの場所は `/etc/linstor/linstor.toml` であり、サテライトの場合は `/etc/linstor/linstor_satellite.toml` です。次のようにログレベルを設定してください:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[logging]\n"
"   level=\"TRACE\"\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"[logging]\n"
"   level=\"TRACE\"\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
". As LINSTOR is using logback as an implementation, `/usr/share/linstor-server/lib/logback.xml`\n"
"  can also be used. Currently only this approach supports different log levels for different\n"
"  components, like shown in the example below:\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
". LINSTORは実装としてlogbackを使用しているため、`/usr/share/linstor-server/lib/logback.xml`も使用することができます。現在、この方法のみがさまざまなコンポーネントに対して異なるログレベルをサポートしており、以下の例に示すように機能します。\n"
"+\n"
"----\n"

#. type: Table
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n"
"<configuration scan=\"false\" scanPeriod=\"60 seconds\">\n"
"<!--\n"
" Values for scanPeriod can be specified in units of milliseconds, seconds, minutes or hours\n"
" https://logback.qos.ch/manual/configuration.html\n"
"-->\n"
" <appender name=\"STDOUT\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender\">\n"
"   <!-- encoders are assigned the type\n"
"        ch.qos.logback.classic.encoder.PatternLayoutEncoder by default -->\n"
"   <encoder>\n"
"     <pattern>%d{HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger - %msg%n</pattern>\n"
"   </encoder>\n"
" </appender>\n"
" <appender name=\"FILE\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender\">\n"
"   <file>${log.directory}/linstor-${log.module}.log</file>\n"
"   <append>true</append>\n"
"   <encoder class=\"ch.qos.logback.classic.encoder.PatternLayoutEncoder\">\n"
"     <Pattern>%d{yyyy_MM_dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger - %msg%n</Pattern>\n"
"   </encoder>\n"
"   <rollingPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.FixedWindowRollingPolicy\">\n"
"     <FileNamePattern>logs/linstor-${log.module}.%i.log.zip</FileNamePattern>\n"
"     <MinIndex>1</MinIndex>\n"
"     <MaxIndex>10</MaxIndex>\n"
"   </rollingPolicy>\n"
"   <triggeringPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.SizeBasedTriggeringPolicy\">\n"
"     <MaxFileSize>2MB</MaxFileSize>\n"
"   </triggeringPolicy>\n"
" </appender>\n"
" <logger name=\"LINSTOR/Controller\" level=\"TRACE\" additivity=\"false\">\n"
"   <appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\" />\n"
"   <!-- <appender-ref ref=\"FILE\" /> -->\n"
" </logger>\n"
" <logger name=\"LINSTOR/Satellite\" level=\"TRACE\" additivity=\"false\">\n"
"   <appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\" />\n"
"   <!-- <appender-ref ref=\"FILE\" /> -->\n"
" </logger>\n"
" <root level=\"WARN\">\n"
"   <appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\" />\n"
"   <!-- <appender-ref ref=\"FILE\" /> -->\n"
" </root>\n"
"</configuration>\n"
"----\n"
msgstr ""
"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n"
"<configuration scan=\"false\" scanPeriod=\"60 seconds\">\n"
"<!--\n"
" Values for scanPeriod can be specified in units of milliseconds, seconds, minutes or hours\n"
" https://logback.qos.ch/manual/configuration.html\n"
"-->\n"
" <appender name=\"STDOUT\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender\">\n"
"   <!-- encoders are assigned the type\n"
"        ch.qos.logback.classic.encoder.PatternLayoutEncoder by default -->\n"
"   <encoder>\n"
"     <pattern>%d{HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger - %msg%n</pattern>\n"
"   </encoder>\n"
" </appender>\n"
" <appender name=\"FILE\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender\">\n"
"   <file>${log.directory}/linstor-${log.module}.log</file>\n"
"   <append>true</append>\n"
"   <encoder class=\"ch.qos.logback.classic.encoder.PatternLayoutEncoder\">\n"
"     <Pattern>%d{yyyy_MM_dd HH:mm:ss.SSS} [%thread] %-5level %logger - %msg%n</Pattern>\n"
"   </encoder>\n"
"   <rollingPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.FixedWindowRollingPolicy\">\n"
"     <FileNamePattern>logs/linstor-${log.module}.%i.log.zip</FileNamePattern>\n"
